HEADWORD: Salt rheum
<hw>Salt" rheum</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A popular
name, esp. in the United States, for various cutaneous eruptions,
particularly for those of eczema. See <er>Eczema</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

